Package: scMaSigPro
Type: Package
Title: Application of MaSigPro Bioconductor Package for scRNA Trajectory data
Version: 1.0.2
Author: Ana Conesa, Maria Jose Nueda and Priyansh Srivastava
Maintainer: Priyansh Srivastava <spriyansh29@gmail.com>
Description: scMaSigPro is a polynomial regression-based approach inspired by
    the MaSigPro Bioconductor package. It discretizes the expression of
    individual cells along pseudotime while preserving the order of cells.
    Subsequently, it applies the maSigPro model to identify genes exhibiting
    significant expression profile differences among branching paths.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: maSigPro, ggplot2, SingleCellExperiment, methods, MASS, assertthat,
    entropy, parallel, dplyr, magrittr, stringr, stats, S4Vectors, e1071,
    MatrixGenerics, igraph, data.table, RColorConesa, UpSetR, utils,
    shiny, plotly, rlang, scales
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Suggests: testthat, roxygen2
Config/testthat/edition: 3
URL: https://github.com/spriyansh/scMaSigPro
biocViews: ScRNA-Seq, Trajectory Differential Expression, Pseudotime,
    Branching Paths, Trajectory Analysis
BugReports: https://github.com/spriyansh/scMaSigPro/issues
